===subject:Well... maybe
===from:Kelcey Larsen-Ferree
===date:Thu Feb 17 18:34:34 2000
===message:I think I would almost agree with you.  But the thing is, I don't think it's even possible to know everything about GM crops and the branching effects they would have on ecological systems.  And because of that, I don't think it will ever be safe to use them.  Most certainly not when they have built-in pesticides.  I don't want to eat food that is used to kill insects, and I'd be even more hesitant to feed it to small children whose bodies would be affected by them more strongly than my adult body would be.  But if there was somehow a way of inserting a gene that would produce some sort of completely harmless scent which the insects disliked and naturally avoided, I might not have a problem with that.  However, I doubt any molecule in existence is completely harmless to every species, so I don't think such a thing is possible.
=========yorg=========
